						               													<description>In &amp;#229;&amp;#145;&amp;#170;&amp;#232;&amp;#161;&amp;#147;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175; (Cursed Tricks), players aim to take the most cards over a series of hands.  Each card taken will be worth 1 point; however, when a player wins a trick, the card that won the trick may &amp;quot;curse&amp;quot; them, causing them not to score cards of that color.  If a player takes a curse of a second color, they cannot score points at all, and if a player collects a third curse, the round ends prematurely and the player scores negative points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Curses may be passed to other players who win a trick of that color with a higher ranked card than the current curse, and curses may be broken by players who follow suit and play the lowest card of that suit to a trick.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most points after a certain number of rounds wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
